{
  "doc_id": "16919",
  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , Kenig and Merle gave a classification of all possible behaviors (blow up or scattering) of solutions whose initial data (u 0 , u 1 ) satisfies E(u 0 , u 1 ) < E(W, 0). Next, in [CITATION_2] , Duyckaerts and Merle studied the threshold case E(u 0 , u 1 ) = E(W, 0) and constructed the stable manifold around W . Then, Duyckaerts, Kenig and Merle [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] proved the following result for solutions slightly above the threshold.",
